# === finding-1a0fa57f-7a3e-477c-acf5-38d67e760a8e ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-1a0fa57f-7a3e-477c-acf5-38d67e760a8e> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-26T14:41:55.043009Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0992cacc-298d-4773-9006-51d343f922be" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-26T14:41:55.042794+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here is the comprehensive research on Amazon's Q4 2025 earnings:\n\n---\n\n## Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings Summary\n*Reported February 5, 2026 (after-hours)*\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & YoY Growth\n\n| Metric | Result | vs. Estimate |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| **Total Revenue** | **$213.4 billion** | Beat ($211.5B est.) |\n| **YoY Growth** | **+14%** | — |\n| **Full-Year 2025 Revenue** | ~**$638B** (implied) | — |\n| **Operating Income** | **$25.0 billion** | — |\n| **Operating Margin** | **11.7%** | — |\n| **Net Income (Q4)** | $21.2 billion | — |\n| **Full-Year Net Income** | $77.7 billion | +31% YoY |\n\n---\n\n### 2. EPS — Actual vs. Estimates\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Diluted EPS (Q4 Actual)** | **$1.95** |\n| **EPS Estimate** | $1.97 |\n| **Miss** | -$0.02 (slight miss) |\n| **YoY EPS (Q4)** | +$0.09 vs. $1.86 in Q4 2024 |\n| **Full-Year 2025 Diluted EPS** | **$7.17** (+30% YoY vs. $5.53) |\n\n**Note:** Q4 included **$2.4 billion of special charges** — $1.1B related to Italian tax disputes and a lawsuit settlement, plus severance and physical store impairments — which weighed on International segment margins and EPS.\n\n---\n\n### 3. AWS Revenue & Growth\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **AWS Revenue** | **$35.6 billion** |\n| **YoY Growth** | **+24%** |\n| **Annualized Run Rate** | **~$142 billion** |\n| **QoQ Revenue Add** | +$2.6 billion |\n| **AWS Operating Income** | **$12.5 billion** |\n| **AWS Operating Margin** | **35%** (+40 bps YoY) |\n| **AWS Contracted Backlog** | **$244 billion** (+40% YoY, +22% QoQ) |\n\nAndy Jassy described this as **\"AWS's fastest growth in 13 quarters\"** — a multi-year acceleration driven by AI workloads absorbing previously constrained capacity.\n\n---\n\n### 4. North America & International Segments\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY Growth | Operating Income | Op. Margin |\n|---------|---------|-----------|-----------------|-----------|\n| **North America** | **$127.1B** | **+10%** | ~$11.5B | **9.0%** (vs. 8.0% prior year) |\n| **International** | **$50.7B** | **+17%** (+11% constant currency) | **$1.0B** | **2.1%** (vs. 3.0% prior year — impacted by $2.4B special charges) |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Advertising Revenue\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Advertising Revenue** | **$21.32 billion** |\n| **YoY Growth** | **+23%** |\n| **Key driver** | Prime Video ad tier expansion |\n\nAdvertising continues to be one of Amazon's highest-margin, fastest-growing lines. Growth was supported by Prime Video inventory added throughout 2025.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Free Cash Flow\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Q4 Free Cash Flow** | **$7.7 billion** (vs. $32.9B in Q4 2024) |\n| **TTM Free Cash Flow** | **$11.2 billion** |\n| **Capex consumed** | ~94.5% of operating cash flow in Q4 |\n\nThe sharp FCF drop was one of the key market concerns. CFO Brian Olsavsky offered **no explicit FCF floor or investment payback timeline**, which unnerved investors.\n\n---\n\n### 7. AI Services Commentary (Bedrock, Trainium, Graviton)\n\n**Amazon Bedrock:**\n- Reached **multi-billion-dollar annualized run rate**\n- Customer spend grew **+60% quarter-over-quarter**\n- Momentum driven by managed models and agentic AI workloads\n\n**Custom Silicon:**\n- Amazon's chips business (Graviton + Trainium combined) exceeded **$10 billion annualized run rate**, growing at **triple-digit percentages YoY**\n\n**Graviton:**\n- Used by **>90% of AWS's top 1,000 customers**\n- Up to **40% more price-performant** than leading x86 processors\n- Growing **>50% YoY** — multi-billion ARR\n\n**Trainium:**\n- **1.4 million Trainium2 chips** deployed\n- Trainium2: **30–40% more price-performant** than comparable GPUs\n- **Trainium3** launched — up to 40% better than Trainium2; **nearly all supply committed by mid-2026**\n- **Trainium4** targeted for 2027; Trainium5 conversations already begun\n\n---\n\n### 8. Q1 2026 Forward Guidance\n\n| Metric | Guidance |\n|--------|----------|\n| **Net Sales** | **$173.5B – $178.5B** |\n| **YoY Revenue Growth** | ~6–9% (sequential step-down from holiday Q4) |\n| **Operating Income** | **$16.5B – $21.5B** |\n| **Key cost headwind** | ~$1B higher YoY costs from **Project Kuiper (Amazon LEO)** satellites; international quick-commerce investment and sharper pricing |\n\n**Note:** The wide operating income range ($16.5B–$21.5B, a **$5B band**) was unusually wide for Amazon, reflecting Kuiper launch uncertainty and international investment discretion.\n\n---\n\n### 9. Capital Expenditure — The Dominant Market Narrative\n\n| Metric | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| **2025 CapEx (actual)** | ~$130 billion |\n| **2026 CapEx (guided)** | **~$200 billion** (+54% YoY) |\n| **Destination** | \"Predominantly AWS\" — Andy Jassy |\n| **Analyst expectation** | ~$146.6 billion |\n| **vs. Estimate** | +$53 billion upside shock |\n\nThis $200B CapEx announcement was the dominant market catalyst — **dwarfing the EPS miss** as the reason for the stock selloff.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Key Executive Commentary\n\n**Andy Jassy (CEO):**\n- AWS backlog of $244B (+40% YoY) represents \"multi-year demand visibility\" — companies are committing to AWS for the long term\n- Framed $200B capex as confidence signal: \"We wouldn't be spending this kind of money if we didn't have very high demand\"\n- Noted AI compute demand was outstripping supply in prior quarters; new capacity coming online is \"immediately useful\"\n- Said Trainium and Graviton together represent a chip business \"growing triple digits\" now above $10B ARR\n- Called out agentic AI and **multi-agent orchestration** as the next frontier — Bedrock's agentic features driving enterprise adoption\n\n**Brian Olsavsky (CFO):**\n- Flagged $2.4B of special charges in Q4 impacting International margins\n- Described FCF pressure as expected, given timing of CapEx vs. depreciation recognition\n- Gave **no FCF floor** or explicit return timeline — the key market disappointment\n- Q1 guidance includes ~$1B incremental cost from **Project Kuiper** (Amazon's satellite broadband constellation, competing with Starlink)\n\n---\n\n### 11. Stock Price Reaction\n\n| Metric | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| **After-hours move (Feb 5)** | **-8% to -10%** |\n| **Primary driver** | $200B CapEx guidance shock + EPS miss |\n| **Secondary factor** | Q1 operating income wide/low guidance range |\n| **Operational sentiment** | Results themselves broadly solid; AWS beat was strong |\n\nThe selloff mirrored Microsoft's pattern — operationally solid results overshadowed by aggressive AI infrastructure spending, raising questions about near-term returns on capital.\n\n---\n\n### Sources\n\n- [Amazon.com Announces Fourth Quarter Results (IR)](https://ir.aboutamazon.com/news-release/news-release-details/2025/Amazon-com-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-Results/)\n- [Amazon Q4 FY 2025: Revenue Beat, AWS +24% Amid $200B Capex Plan — Futurum Group](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/amazon-q4-fy-2025-revenue-beat-aws-24-amid-200b-capex-plan/)\n- [Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings: The $200B Infrastructure Mandate — Global Data Center Hub](https://www.globaldatacenterhub.com/p/amazon-q4-2025-earnings-the-200b)\n- [Amazon stock falls 8% on $200B spending forecast, earnings miss — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [Andy Jassy on AWS $244B Backlog, Trainium4 and AI Chips Strategy — CRN Australia](https://www.crn.com.au/news-network/cloud/2026/andy-jassy-on-aws-244b-backlog)\n- [Amazon (AMZN) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript — Motley Fool](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [Amazon Q4 2025 Slides: Revenue Jumps 14%, AWS Growth Accelerates to 24% — Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/company-news/amazon-q4-2025-slides-revenue-jumps-14-aws-growth-accelerates-to-24-93CH-4489269)\n- [Amazon Reports $213B Q4 2025 Sales — Techloy](https://www.techloy.com/amazon-reports-213b-q4-2025-sales-and-plans-200b-ai-spending-surge-as-free-cash-flow-drops/)\n- [Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings Call Highlights — Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/amazon-com-q4-earnings-call-010627319.html)\n- [Amazon Earnings Q4 2025 Official Report — aboutamazon.com](https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/company-news/amazon-earnings-q4-2025-report)\n- [SEC Filing — Q4 2025 Earnings Release (PDF)](https://s2.q4cdn.com/299287126/files/doc_earnings/2025/q4/earnings-result/AMZN-Q4-2025-Earnings-Release.pdf)" ;
