loud's 48% growth outpaced both Azure (+39%) and AWS (~+17.5%) in the quarter — the strongest growth rate among the three hyperscalers.\n\n---\n\n### 5. YouTube Advertising Revenue\n\n| Metric | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Q4 Ads Revenue** | **$11.38B** (+~9% YoY) |\n| **Estimate** | $11.84B — **missed** |\n| **Full Year 2025 (Ads + Subscriptions)** | **>$60 billion** (milestone crossed) |\n\nThe YouTube ads miss was the one soft spot in an otherwise strong report. Management did not provide a specific explanation for the shortfall vs. estimates.\n\n---\n\n### 6. AI Overviews & Gemini Monetization\n\n- **AI Overviews / AI Mode**: Management credited AI Overviews in Search for driving the 17% Search revenue growth. Users are conducting **more and longer queries**, and commercial query volumes are expanding — not cannibalizing.\n- **No Search cannibalization**: Management explicitly stated there is \"no evidence\" that the Gemini app is cannibalizing Search; instead, the two are complementary.\n- **Gemini 3**: Launched during the quarter — Pichai called it \"a major milestone.\"\n- **Gemini App MAU**: Reached **750 million monthly active users**.\n- **Gemini API usage**: Processing **10 billion+ tokens per minute** via direct customer API calls.\n- **Enterprise adoption**: 8M+ paid Gemini Enterprise seats; Gemini for Workspace broadly adopted.\n- **Cost efficiency**: Serving unit costs reduced **78% over the course of 2025** through model optimization, efficiency, and utilization improvements — critical for margin expansion as AI scales.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Forward Guidance & CapEx Plans\n\n| Metric | Guidance |\n|--------|----------|\n| **2026 CapEx** | **$175B – $185B** |\n| **2025 CapEx (actual)** | ~$91.4 billion |\n| **YoY CapEx increase** | **~+92% to +103%** — nearly doubling |\n| **CapEx allocation** | ~60% servers, ~40% data centers & networking |\n\nThis was the most market-moving disclosure. The $175B–$185B capex range was described as targeting:\n- AI compute capacity for **Google DeepMind**\n- Meeting **\"significant cloud customer demand\"**\n- **Strategic investments in Other Bets**\n\nRuth Porat also flagged a **growing mismatch between AI demand and U.S. power supply** as a structural challenge for the buildout.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Key Executive Commentary\n\n**Sundar Pichai (CEO):**\n- *\"It was a tremendous quarter for Alphabet and annual revenues exceeded $400 billion for the first time.\"*\n- *\"The launch of Gemini 3 was a major milestone and we have great momentum.\"*\n- Described Search as being in **\"an expansionary moment\"** driven by AI features.\n- Emphasized that AI Overviews and AI Mode expand total query volume — including commercial queries — rather than substituting for them.\n\n**Ruth Porat (President & CIO):**\n- Focused on financial discipline around massive infrastructure investment.\n- Highlighted the **power supply bottleneck** as a key constraint on AI infrastructure scaling in the U.S.\n- Presented the $240B cloud backlog as evidence of durable demand justifying the capex acceleration.\n\n---\n\n### 9. GOOGL Stock Reaction\n\n| Metric | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| **After-hours move (Feb 4)** | **-3%** despite EPS + revenue beat |\n| **Primary concern** | Massive capex surge ($175B–$185B for 2026) raising ROI questions |\n| **Secondary concern** | YouTube ads miss vs. estimates |\n| **Analyst response post-earnings** | Price targets broadly lifted; bullish consensus maintained |\n\nThe pattern mirrored Microsoft's earnings reaction — strong fundamentals overshadowed by capex anxiety. However, GOOGL's -3% drop was far more muted than MSFT's -12% intraday low, suggesting markets viewed Google's AI monetization trajectory more favorably (evidenced by Cloud's 48% growth and Search's AI-driven expansion).\n\n---\n\n### 10. Ad Tech & Cloud Sector Context\n\n| Dynamic | Detail |\n|---------|--------|\n| **Search durability** | +17% YoY growth amid AI disruption fears validates Search's resilience |\n| **AI Overviews monetization** | Expanding commercial queries = positive read-through for ad tech |\n| **Google Network -2%** | Continued structural headwind for third-party publisher ad networks (programmatic/open web) |\n| **YouTube miss** | Modest negative signal for streaming/video ad market; competitors (Meta, TikTok) may be taking share |\n| **Cloud 48% growth** | Strongest hyperscaler growth rate; positive for cloud-adjacent software and AI infrastructure names |\n| **$240B Cloud backlog** | Enterprise AI spending cycle is accelerating, not plateauing |\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- [Alphabet Q4 2025 earnings — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings.html)\n- [Official Alphabet Earnings Release (Q4CDN PDF)](https://s206.q4cdn.com/479360582/files/doc_financials/2025/q4/2025q4-alphabet-earnings-release.pdf)\n- [Alphabet Investor Relations Press Release](https://abc.xyz/investor/news/news-details/2026/Alphabet-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-2025-and-Fiscal-Year-Results-2026-KEvZIMKBLS/default.aspx)\n- [9to5Google — Alphabet Q4 2025](https://9to5google.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-q4-2025-earnings/)\n- [Benzinga — Google Cloud Up 48%, YouTube Tops $60B](https://www.benzinga.com/markets/earnings/26/02/50396139/alphabet-q4-highlights-google-cloud-revenue-up-48-youtube-tops-60-billion-for-2025)\n- [Google Blog — Sundar Pichai CEO Remarks](https://blog.google/company-news/inside-google/message-ceo/alphabet-earnings-q4-2025/)\n- [Motley Fool — Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [Storyboard18 — Ad Revenue $82.3B, YouTube $11.4B](https://www.storyboard18.com/advertising/google-posts-82-3-billion-of-ad-revenue-youtubes-advertising-business-hit-11-4-billion-in-q4-2025-88901.htm)\n- [IEEE ComSoc — Capex Forecast & Gemini 3](https://techblog.comsoc.org/2026/02/04/alphabets-2026-forecast-capex-soars-gemini-3-ai-model-is-a-huge-success/)\n