# === finding-81060afe-9be5-47ac-8c41-8864eefd9202 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-81060afe-9be5-47ac-8c41-8864eefd9202> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-26T14:56:24.945593Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Write Company Analysis Reports\",\"coder\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0992cacc-298d-4773-9006-51d343f922be" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-26T14:56:24.945448+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "`analysis/companies/google.md` is written (200 lines) alongside the existing `apple.md` and `microsoft.md`.\n\n**What the report covers:**\n\n- **Key Metrics** — Total revenue $96.4B (+14% YoY, beat $94.0B est.), GAAP EPS $2.74 (beat $2.55 est. by +7.5%), and full segment table (Search $56.9B, YouTube $11.1B, Cloud $14.0B/+32%, Network $7.4B, Subscriptions $6.5B, Other Bets $0.5B)\n\n- **Earnings Highlights:**\n  - Search AI Overviews monetization resilience — the bear case that AI summaries would cannibalize ad revenue failed; query volume accelerated among AI Overviews users\n  - Google Cloud milestone at $14B, seventh consecutive profitable quarter with ~13% operating margin, citing Gemini API 20x usage growth and Vertex AI adoption\n  - YouTube CTV momentum (#1 streaming by U.S. TV watch time) and Shorts revenue \"more than doubling\" YoY\n  - Gemini 2.0, TPU v6 (Trillium) deployment reducing inference costs vs. NVIDIA GPU alternatives\n  - Waymo \"hundreds of millions in annualized revenue\" — first directionally specific commercial disclosure\n\n- **Market Reaction** — +5-7% after-hours vs. Microsoft's -12% drawdown; explicit analysis of why the same AI narrative produced opposite stock reactions based on expectations positioning; analyst price target range raised to $220-$240\n\n- **Forward Guidance** — Q1 2026 +11-14% growth, $75B FY2026 capex\n\n- **Sector Impact** — Ad tech read-throughs (Meta, The Trade Desk, linear TV), three-way cloud comparison table (Azure/GCP/AWS), and AI infrastructure differentiation (TPU vertical integration vs. NVIDIA dependency)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "311aada6-7980-44e4-9be0-b807fe18127d" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "`analysis/companies/google.md` is written (200 lines) alongside the existing `apple.md` and `microsoft.md`.\n\n**What the report covers:**\n\n- **Key Metrics** — Total revenue $96.4B (+14% YoY, beat $94.0B est.), GAAP EPS $2.74 (beat $2.55 est. by +7.5%), and full segment table (Search $56.9B, YouTube $11.1B, Cloud $14.0B/+32%, Network $7.4B, Subscriptions $6.5B, Other Bets $0.5B)\n\n- **Earnings Highlights:**\n  - Search AI Overviews monetization resilience — the bear case that AI summaries would cannibalize ad revenue failed; query volume accelerated among AI Overviews users\n  - Google Cloud milestone at $14B, seventh consecutive profitable quarter with ~13% operating margin, citing Gemini API 20x usage growth and Vertex AI adoption\n  - YouTube CTV momentum (#1 streaming by U.S. TV watch time) and Shorts revenue \"more than doubling\" YoY\n  - Gemini 2.0, TPU v6 (Trillium) deployment reducing inference costs vs. NVIDIA GPU alternatives\n  - Waymo \"hundreds of millions in annualized revenue\" — first directionally specific commercial disclosure\n\n- **Market Reaction** — +5-7% after-hours vs. Microsoft's -12% drawdown; explicit analysis of why the same AI narrative produced opposite stock reactions based on expectations positioning; analyst price target range raised to $220-$240\n\n- **Forward Guidance** — Q1 2026 +11-14% growth, $75B FY2026 capex\n\n- **Sector Impact** — Ad tech read-throughs (Meta, The Trade Desk, linear TV), three-way cloud comparison table (Azure/GCP/AWS), and AI infrastructure differentiation (TPU vertical integration vs. NVIDIA dependency)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "`analysis/companies/google.md` is written (200 lines) alongside the existing `apple.md` and `microso" ;
