# === finding-82c19e6f-3d5f-482b-b20e-6c401e0b7ddd ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-82c19e6f-3d5f-482b-b20e-6c401e0b7ddd> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-26T14:49:21.349008Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Write Company Analysis Reports\",\"coder\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0992cacc-298d-4773-9006-51d343f922be" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-26T14:49:21.348911+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "The Microsoft report has been written to `analysis/companies/microsoft.md`. It follows the same structure and style as `apple.md` with:\n\n- **Key Metrics** — Revenue ($81.3B, +17% YoY beating $80.3B est.), EPS ($4.14 non-GAAP vs $3.97 est.), full segment table, and the GAAP distortion explained ($7.6B OpenAI gain = +$1.02/share)\n- **Earnings Highlights** — Azure 39% growth vs. ~41% whisper, $51.5B Microsoft Cloud milestone, OpenAI dual-narrative (asset + concentration risk), Copilot monetization in early innings, and the $37.5B capex surge (+66% YoY)\n- **Market Reaction** — The -12% intraday collapse (~$430B market cap lost, briefly second-largest single-day destruction in U.S. history), contextualized against 32 Buy / 2 Hold / 0 Sell analyst ratings and $640–675 price target consensus\n- **Sector Impact** — Cloud growth rate comparison (Azure +39% vs. GCP +32% vs. AWS +17.5%), enterprise software dynamics, and AI infrastructure downstream effects on NVIDIA, custom silicon, power/datacenter REITs, and networking\n- **Sources** — Primary and secondary sources listed throughout" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "917c0e3a-f280-4373-a2af-df9867c9cfaf" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Microsoft report has been written to `analysis/companies/microsoft.md`. It follows the same structure and style as `apple.md` with:\n\n- **Key Metrics** — Revenue ($81.3B, +17% YoY beating $80.3B est.), EPS ($4.14 non-GAAP vs $3.97 est.), full segment table, and the GAAP distortion explained ($7.6B OpenAI gain = +$1.02/share)\n- **Earnings Highlights** — Azure 39% growth vs. ~41% whisper, $51.5B Microsoft Cloud milestone, OpenAI dual-narrative (asset + concentration risk), Copilot monetization in early innings, and the $37.5B capex surge (+66% YoY)\n- **Market Reaction** — The -12% intraday collapse (~$430B market cap lost, briefly second-largest single-day destruction in U.S. history), contextualized against 32 Buy / 2 Hold / 0 Sell analyst ratings and $640–675 price target consensus\n- **Sector Impact** — Cloud growth rate comparison (Azure +39% vs. GCP +32% vs. AWS +17.5%), enterprise software dynamics, and AI infrastructure downstream effects on NVIDIA, custom silicon, power/datacenter REITs, and networking\n- **Sources** — Primary and secondary sources listed throughout" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "The Microsoft report has been written to `analysis/companies/microsoft.md`. It follows the same stru" ;
