	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "`analysis/companies/amazon.md` has been written. The report follows the same structure and analytical tone as `apple.md` and covers:\n\n- **Key Metrics** — Revenue ($213.4B, beat), EPS ($1.95 slight miss due to $2.4B special charges), and segment table with operating margins\n- **Earnings Highlights** — AWS \"fastest growth in 13 quarters\" (+24%, $244B backlog), holiday e-commerce with North America margin expansion (8.0% → 9.0%), advertising as margin driver, the structural margin story, special charges breakdown, and management commentary/guidance\n- **Market Reaction** — Stock positive post-earnings despite EPS miss; analyst focus on AWS reacceleration and margin record\n- **Forward Guidance** — Q1 2026 at $151–155.5B revenue, $14–18B operating income with wide range reflecting capex depreciation timing\n- **Sector Impact** — Cloud positioning (AWS vs. Azure vs. GCP with absolute dollar comparison), e-commerce/retail competitive dynamics, advertising's structural moat, and logistics network compounding advantage\n- **Sources** — Primary and secondary sources listed" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
