pend in 2026**.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Stock Reaction & Analyst Sentiment\n\n| Metric | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **After-hours drop (Feb 5)** | **–11.5%** (capex guidance shock) |\n| **Next-day decline** | –4.56% regular session, –2.46% after-hours |\n| **Mid-March recovery level** | ~$210–$215/share |\n| **Consensus price target** | **$286.93** (58 analysts; 53 Buy, 4 Hold, 1 Strong Buy) |\n| **Total ratings** | 67 Buy/Strong Buy, 4 Hold, 0 Sell |\n\n**Notable analyst actions:** DZ Bank upgraded to Strong Buy; Citigroup trimmed target from $320 → $265 (citing FCF compression risk); consensus ~$280–$287 implies ~33–37% upside from post-earnings levels.\n\n**Bull case:** $244B AWS backlog de-risks deceleration; $68.6B ad business is high-margin and accelerating; $200B capex is demand-driven; Trainium at $10B+ creates long-term margin upside.\n\n**Bear case:** FCF compressed by capex; AWS losing % share to Azure/GCP; $200B execution risk unprecedented; slight EPS miss ($1.95 vs. $1.97 est.); P/E near 5-year lows.\n\n---\n\n### Cross-Sector Scorecard\n\n| Sector | Direction | Key Takeaway |\n|---|---|---|\n| Cloud (AWS) | Positive | Fastest growth in 13 qtrs; $244B backlog; losing % share to Azure/GCP |\n| E-commerce | Positive | Record same-day delivery; 35.7% U.S. share |\n| Advertising | Strongly Positive | $21.3B Q4 (+23%); outpacing Google's growth rate |\n| Amazon Logistics | Positive | #1 U.S. carrier by volume; same-day +70% |\n| UPS | Negative | –10.8% Q4 volume; cutting Amazon by 50% by mid-2026 |\n| FedEx | Neutral/Positive | New Amazon deal; market cap now exceeds UPS |\n| AI Chips (Trainium/Graviton) | Strongly Positive | $10B+ run rate, triple-digit growth; Trainium3 sold out |\n| Nvidia/AMD/Broadcom | Positive | +5–6% on capex news; 1M GPU deal confirmed |\n| AMZN Stock | Mixed | Revenue beat, EPS miss; –11.5% AH on $200B capex shock; partial recovery |" ;
