	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-26T14:32:43.592277+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here is the compiled research on Apple's Q4 2025 (FY Q1 2026) earnings impact across related sectors:\n\n---\n\n## Sector Impact: Apple FY Q1 2026 Earnings (Reported Jan 29, 2026)\n\n---\n\n### 1. AAPL Stock Price Reaction\n\n- **After-hours move on Jan 29:** +0.46% — strikingly muted\n- **Options-implied expected move:** ±3.83% (~$9.88/share)\n- **Context:** Despite a massive revenue and EPS beat, the stock barely moved, suggesting the blowout quarter was already priced in; the \"buy the rumor, sell the news\" dynamic was in play\n- Apple was up going into earnings as iPhone 17 demand data had already leaked via Foxconn and TSMC channel checks\n\n---\n\n### 2. Semiconductor Sector\n\n**TSMC (direct beneficiary):**\n- TSMC reported Q4 earnings on Jan 15, 2026 (pre-Apple earnings): revenue **$33.73B** vs $33.1B consensus; EPS **$19.50** vs $17.89 expected\n- Q1 2026 guidance raised to **$34.6–$35.8B** with gross margins of **63–65%**\n- ASML crossed **$500B market cap** following TSMC's blowout, pulling semiconductor ETFs up broadly\n- TSMC N2 (2nm) ramp: from 50K wafers/month currently to a target of **140K by year-end 2026**\n\n**Apple's TSMC supply constraint — a key narrative:**\n- Apple explicitly acknowledged on the earnings call that it is **constrained by TSMC's supply of advanced chips** AND storage/memory supply — CFO Kevan Parekh incorporated these constraints into Q2 guidance\n- Apple has reserved **50%+ of TSMC's entire 2nm capacity** for A20/M5/R2 chips launching in fall 2026\n- Nvidia is now competing directly with Apple for TSMC foundry capacity — described as a shift from a \"unipolar\" (Apple-dominated) to a \"bipolar\" (Apple + AI) demand dynamic, giving TSMC significant pricing power\n- [Tom's Hardware](https://www.tomshardware.com/tech-industry/semiconductors/apple-concedes-it-is-constrained-by-tsmcs-supply-of-advanced-chips-storage-and-memory-are-also-in-short-supply-firm-isnt-projecting-supply-conditions-beyond-the-second-quarter) | [AppleInsider](https://appleinsider.com/articles/26/01/16/nvidia-is-squeezing-out-apple-for-tsmc-foundry-capacity) | [Dataconomy](https://dataconomy.com/2025/11/12/apple-reserves-over-50-of-tsmc-2nm-capacity-for-2026/)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Consumer Electronics Supply Chain\n\n**Foxconn (primary iPhone assembler):**\n- Q4 2025 revenue: **+22.07% YoY** to T$2.6028 trillion (~$82.73B) — record high, beat LSEG consensus of T$2.418T\n- January 2026 revenue: **+35.53% YoY** to NT$730B — strongest January on record\n- Notable structural shift: **AI server/cloud infrastructure** (42% of revenue) has now surpassed smart consumer electronics as Foxconn's top segment — iPhone assembly revenue is growing but losing share within Foxconn's own mix\n- Foxconn guided Q1 2026 seasonality stronger than 5-year average\n- [MacDailyNews](https://macdailynews.com/2026/01/05/apple-assembler-foxconns-q4-revenue-jumps-22-to-record-high/) | [Digitimes](https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260202PD200/foxconn-apple-assembly-iphone-recovery.html)\n\n**Qualcomm (modem supplier — transitioning out):**\n- Apple's in-house modem debuted in iPhone SE (spring 2025); full-iPhone modem transition not until **2028** (end of Qualcomm licensing agreement)\n- Qualcomm's annual Apple modem revenue: **~$5.7–5.9B** + ~$1.6–1.9B in RF components\n- QCOM stock **down ~24–25% YTD as of March 2026** — partially driven by Apple modem transition overhang and China headwinds\n- Long-term revenue at risk: **$4–6B annually** once Apple fully transitions\n- [Barchart](https://www.barchart.com/story/news/37025790/ignore-the-apple-noise-and-consider-buying-qualcomm-stock-for-2026) | [Bloomberg](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-12-06/apple-s-three-year-modem-road-map-company-plans-to-beat-qualcomm-by-2027)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Services / App Economy\n\n- Services hit **$30.0B** (+14% YoY) — all-time record; Apple guided similar growth rate for Q2 FY2026\n- Records were set in: advertising, cloud (iCloud), music, and payment services (Apple Pay)\n- App Store has now generated **$550B+ cumulative developer earnings** since 2008; 2024 US billings/sales: **$406B** facilitated\n- Apple expanding App Store advertising inventory (new search placements), signaling higher monetization from the developer ecosystem\n- [Variety](https://variety.com/2026/digital/news/apple-earnings-q1-2026-iphone-sales-services-1236644631/) | [Fifth Person](https://fifthperson.com/apple-q1-2026/)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Analyst Upgrades / Downgrades Post-Earnings\n\n| Firm | Action | Price Target | Date |\n|------|--------|-------------|------|\n| **Maxim Group** | Raised target | **$300** | Jan 30, 2026 |\n| **Loop Capital** | Upgraded: Hold → Buy | **$315** | Post-earnings |\n| **Citi** | Raised target | **$330** | Post-earnings |\n| **Wedbush (Dan Ives)** | Maintained Buy | **$310** (Street high: $350) | Post-earnings |\n| **Raymond James** | Downgraded: Outperform → Market Perform | N/A | Jan 2026 |\n\n- Consensus: **28 analysts → Buy rating** as of March 24, 2026; average price target **~$297.58** (MarketBeat)\n- Raymond James downgrade cited: stretched valuation, priced-in iPhone strength, AI catalyst skepticism, foldable iPhone uncertainty\n- [MarketBeat](https://www.marketbeat.com/stocks/NASDAQ/AAPL/forecast/) | [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/apple-stock-starts-2026-downgrade-154205170.html)\n\n---\n\n### Key Takeaways\n\n1. **Semiconductors:** Apple's record quarter validated TSMC's dominance and triggered a broader semis rally. The real story is Apple being *supply-constrained by TSMC* — a reversal of historical dynamics now that Nvidia competes for the same nodes.\n2. **Consumer electronics supply chain:** Foxconn is thriving but AI servers are now its core growth driver, not iPhones. Apple demand is strong but no longer the sole locomotive.\n3. **Qualcomm:** Structural overhang continues — modem transition timeline (2028) is a known headwind weighing on QCOM regardless of Apple's blowout quarter.\n4. **Stock reaction:** Muted (+0.46% AH) despite massive beat — market had front-run the results via supply chain data.\n5. **Services:** $30B/quarter run rate positions Services as an increasingly important earnings cushion, reducing Apple's cyclical dependence on hardware.\n\nSources:\n- [Apple Q1 2026 Press Release](https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2026/01/apple-reports-first-quarter-results/)\n- [Tom's Hardware — TSMC supply constraint](https://www.tomshardware.com/tech-industry/semiconductors/apple-concedes-it-is-constrained-by-tsmcs-supply-of-advanced-chips-storage-and-memory-are-also-in-short-supply-firm-isnt-projecting-supply-conditions-beyond-the-second-quarter)\n- [AppleInsider — Nvidia vs Apple at TSMC](https://appleinsider.com/articles/26/01/16/nvidia-is-squeezing-out-apple-for-tsmc-foundry-capacity)\n- [Dataconomy — Apple 2nm capacity reservation](https://dataconomy.com/2025/11/12/apple-reserves-over-50-of-tsmc-2nm-capacity-for-2026/)\n- [MacDailyNews — Foxconn Q4 record](https://macdailynews.com/2026/01/05/apple-assembler-foxconns-q4-revenue-jumps-22-to-record-high/)\n- [Digitimes — Foxconn iPhone assembly](https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260202PD200/foxconn-apple-assembly-iphone-recovery.html)\n- [247 Wall St — Chip stocks after TSMC blowout](https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/01/15/after-taiwan-semis-earnings-blowout-these-3-chip-stocks-are-positioned-to-dominate/)\n- [Barchart — Qualcomm/Apple modem](https://www.barchart.com/story/news/37025790/ignore-the-apple-noise-and-consider-buying-qualcomm-stock-for-2026)\n- [Variety — Apple Q1 2026 overview](https://variety.com/2026/digital/news/apple-earnings-q1-2026-iphone-sales-services-1236644631/)\n- [MarketBeat — Analyst price targets](https://www.marketbeat.com/stocks/NASDAQ/AAPL/forecast/)\n- [Yahoo Finance — Raymond James downgrade](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/apple-stock-starts-2026-downgrade-154205170.html)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
