	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "7a59a62f-ecc2-4543-9863-2381c645f841" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Here is a comprehensive summary of Apple's fiscal Q1 2026 earnings findings:\n\n---\n\n## Apple Fiscal Q1 2026 Earnings Summary\n*Reported January 29, 2026 — Calendar Q4 2025*\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & YoY Growth\n\n| Metric | Result | vs. Estimate |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| **Total Revenue** | **$143.8 billion** | Beat ($138.48B est.) |\n| **YoY Growth** | **+16%** | — |\n| **Net Income** | $42.1 billion | All-time record |\n| **Operating Cash Flow** | ~$54 billion | — |\n\nApple called this its **\"best quarter ever\"** — a new all-time revenue record.\n\n---\n\n### 2. EPS — Actual vs. Estimates\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Diluted EPS (Actual)** | **$2.84** |\n| **EPS Estimate** | $2.67 |\n| **YoY EPS Growth** | +19% |\n\nBeat consensus by ~$0.17 (a ~6.4% upside surprise).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Segment Revenue Breakdown\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY Change |\n|---------|---------|-----------|\n| **iPhone** | **$85.27B** | **+23%** ✅ All-time record |\n| **Services** | **$30.0B** | **+14%** ✅ All-time record |\n| **Wearables, Home & Accessories** | $11.49B | -2% (supply-constrained) |\n| **iPad** | $8.60B | +6% |\n| **Mac** | $8.39B | -7% |\n\n**Notable:**\n- iPhone 17 family drove the surge; Tim Cook called demand **\"simply staggering\"**\n- Services set records in advertising, cloud, music, and payment services\n- Wearables miss attributed to **AirPods Pro 3 supply constraints** — management said the category would have grown without them\n- China/Greater China revenue surged **+38% YoY** to $25.53 billion\n- Active installed base reached **2.5 billion devices** (up from 2.35B a year prior)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Forward Guidance (Q2 FY2026 / March Quarter)\n\n| Metric | Guidance |\n|--------|----------|\n| **Revenue Growth (YoY)** | **+13% to +16%** |\n| **Gross Margin** | 48% – 49% |\n| **Operating Expenses** | $18.4B – $18.7B |\n\nCFO Kevan Parekh noted guidance incorporates **\"best estimates of constrained iPhone supply\"** during Q2. Memory pricing expected to be a slightly greater headwind vs. Q1.\n\nQ1 actual gross margin came in at **48.2%** (within the prior guidance range).\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Earnings Call Commentary\n\n**Tim Cook (CEO):**\n- Called iPhone 17 **\"by far the most popular\"** iPhone lineup ever\n- Described iPhone demand as **\"simply staggering\"**\n- Highlighted double-digit Services growth as a structural, recurring tailwind\n- Called out China strength as a sign of brand resilience in a critical market\n\n**Kevan Parekh (CFO):**\n- Noted Q1 gross margin benefited from **favorable product mix** (iPhone 17 halo + Services)\n- Flagged **memory pricing** as a modest headwind moving into Q2\n- Emphasized Apple Intelligence features as a driver of upgrade cycle acceleration\n- Returned ~$32 billion to shareholders in Q1 (dividends + buybacks); declared $0.26/share dividend payable Feb 12, 2026\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Apple Q1 2026 Earnings Report — Apple Newsroom](https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2026/01/apple-reports-first-quarter-results/)\n- [Apple AAPL Q1 2026 Earnings — CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/29/apple-aapl-earnings-report-q1-2026.html)\n- [Apple Q1 2026 Record $143.8B Revenue — MacRumors](https://www.macrumors.com/2026/01/29/apple-1q-2026-earnings/)\n- [Apple Q1 2026 Earnings — The Desk](https://thedesk.net/2026/01/apple-fiscal-q1-2026-earnings-report/)\n- [Apple Q1 2026 Earnings Explained by Cook & Parekh — MacObserver](https://www.macobserver.com/news/apples-q1-2026-earnings-explained-by-tim-cook-and-cfo-kevan-parekh/)\n- [Apple Q1 2026 Earnings Call Transcript — Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-apple-q1-2026-earnings-beat-expectations-93CH-4474928)\n- [Apple Q1 2026 Earnings Highlights — Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/apple-inc-aapl-q1-2026-050239886.html)\n- [Apple Q1 2026 Segment Breakdown — Fifth Person](https://fifthperson.com/apple-q1-2026/)\n- [Apple Q1 2026 Earnings Call Transcript — Motley Fool](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/01/29/apple-aapl-q1-2026-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [Apple Q1 2026 — TweakTown](https://www.tweaktown.com/news/109957/apple-posts-its-best-quarter-ever-with-fiscal-q1-2026-earnings-revenue-of-dollars143-8-billion/index.html)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "[researcher] Here is a comprehensive summary of Apple's fiscal Q1 2026 earnings findings:\n\n--" ;
	a <https://schema.org/EpisodicMemory> .


# === memory-b90c2012-14ff-4a73-9157-37ec1175ff2e ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-b90c2012-14ff-4a73-9157-37ec1175ff2e> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-26T14:34:14.226554Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Microsoft Q4 2025 Earnings\",\"Search Microsoft earnings results\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "researcher" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "0992cacc-298d-4773-9006-51d343f922be" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-26T14:34:14.225870+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Here is the comprehensive research on Microsoft's Q2 FY2026 (calendar Q4 2025) earnings:\n\n---\n\n## Microsoft Q2 FY2026 Earnings Summary\n*Reported January 28, 2026 — Calendar Q4 2025*\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & YoY Growth\n\n| Metric | Result | vs. Estimate |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| **Total Revenue** | **$81.3 billion** | Beat ($80.3B est.) |\n| **YoY Growth** | **+17%** (+15% constant currency) | — |\n| **Operating Income** | $38.3 billion | +21% YoY |\n| **Operating Margin** | 47% | — |\n| **Microsoft Cloud Revenue** | $51.5 billion | +26% YoY — first time above $50B |\n\n---\n\n### 2. EPS — Actual vs. Estimates\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Non-GAAP Diluted EPS** | **$4.14** |\n| **EPS Estimate** | $3.97 |\n| **Non-GAAP EPS YoY Growth** | +24% |\n| **GAAP Diluted EPS** | $5.16 (+60%) |\n\n**Important GAAP note:** GAAP EPS was inflated by **$1.02/share** due to a net investment gain of **$7.6 billion from OpenAI**. The non-GAAP figure ($4.14) is the operative comparable. OpenAI also represented **45% of Microsoft's commercial remaining performance obligation (RPO) backlog** — a disclosure that drew significant attention.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Segment Revenue Breakdown\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY Growth |\n|---------|---------|-----------|\n| **Intelligent Cloud** | **$32.9B** | **+29%** |\n| **Productivity & Business Processes** | **$34.1B** | **+16%** (+14% CC) |\n| **More Personal Computing** | **$14.3B** | **-3%** |\n\n**Productivity & Business Processes detail:**\n- Microsoft 365 Commercial cloud: +17% (+14% CC)\n- LinkedIn: +11% (+10% CC)\n- Dynamics 365: +19% (+17% CC)\n\n**More Personal Computing detail:**\n- Search & news advertising (ex-TAC): +10%\n- Xbox content & services: -5%\n- Xbox hardware: -32%\n\n---\n\n### 4. Azure Growth Rate\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Azure & other cloud services YoY growth** | **+39%** (+38% constant currency) |\n\nThis marked an acceleration from prior quarters and was the headline result. Azure AI services represented a meaningful and growing portion of total Azure growth, with AI contributing roughly 13 percentage points of Azure's growth (per management commentary).\n\n---\n\n### 5. AI Revenue & Copilot Metrics\n\n| Metric | Figure |\n|--------|--------|\n| **AI Annual Revenue Run Rate** | **~$26 billion** |\n| **M365 Copilot paid seats** | **15 million** (+160% YoY) |\n| **M365 Copilot daily active users** | Up **10x YoY** |\n| **Conversations per M365 Copilot user** | Doubled YoY |\n| **GitHub Copilot paid subscribers** | **4.7 million** (+75% YoY) |\n| **First-party Copilot MAUs** | **150 million+** across all products |\n| **Fortune 500 with active agents** | **80%+** using Copilot Studio or Agent Builder |\n| **Purview Copilot audits** | 24 billion interactions in the quarter (+9x YoY) |\n\n---\n\n### 6. Forward Guidance (Q3 FY2026)\n\n| Metric | Guidance |\n|--------|----------|\n| **Total Revenue** | $80.65B – $81.75B |\n| **Productivity & Business Processes** | $34.25B – $34.55B |\n| **Intelligent Cloud** | $34.1B – $34.4B |\n| **Azure growth (CC)** | **37% – 38%** |\n| **Microsoft Cloud gross margin** | ~65% (down YoY due to AI infra investment) |\n| **Capital Expenditures** | Elevated; $37.5B spent in Q2 (two-thirds on short-lived assets: GPUs/CPUs) |\n\n---\n\n### 7. Key Executive Commentary\n\n**Satya Nadella (CEO):**\n- *\"We are only at the beginning phases of AI diffusion and already Microsoft has built an AI business that is larger than some of our biggest franchises.\"*\n- Framed company strategy across three layers: **\"cloud and token factory,\" \"agent platform,\" and \"high-value agentic experiences.\"**\n- Declared: *\"You can think of agents as the new apps\"* — positioning the next wave of AI as agentic workflows replacing traditional software.\n- Emphasized Microsoft's AI should be evaluated holistically (M365 Copilot + GitHub Copilot + Security Copilot + Azure AI), not just Azure AI alone.\n\n**Amy Hood (CFO):**\n- Cloud gross margin guidance of ~65% flagged as a deliberate investment decision, not a structural weakness.\n- Flagged that Azure AI capacity constraints were easing and would support re-acceleration into H2 FY2026.\n- Noted Azure guidance of 37–38% CC for Q3 was in-line with or slightly above consensus (~37.1%).\n\n---\n\n### 8. Stock Reaction\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **MSFT pre-earnings price** | ~$480.58 (Jan 27) |\n| **MSFT post-earnings price** | ~$433.50 (Jan 29) |\n| **After-hours move** | **-7%** |\n\nDespite beating on both revenue and EPS, the stock sold off sharply. Key investor concerns:\n1. **Record capex of $37.5B** — investors worried about margin compression from AI infrastructure spend\n2. **Azure guidance of 37–38%** came in roughly in-line but not above consensus, disappointing growth investors who expected acceleration\n3. **OpenAI's 45% share of RPO backlog** raised concentration/dependency concerns\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Microsoft FY26 Q2 Press Release (official)](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q2/press-release-webcast)\n- [Microsoft FY26 Q2 Segment Results (official)](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q2/segment-revenues)\n- [Futurum: Microsoft Q2 FY2026 — Cloud Surpasses $50B, Azure Up 38% CC](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)\n- [CNBC: Microsoft MSFT Q2 Earnings Report 2026](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)\n- [Microsoft Source: Cloud and AI Strength Drives Second Quarter Results](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/)\n- [Yahoo Finance: Microsoft Q2 Earnings Beat Estimates](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/microsoft-q2-earnings-beat-estimates-155700958.html)\n- [Investing.com: Earnings Call Transcript Q2 2026](https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-microsoft-q2-2026-sees-strong-earnings-beat-stock-rises-93CH-4471700)\n- [Tom's Guide: Satya Nadella Q2 2026 Earnings Live](https://www.tomsguide.com/news/live/microsoft-q2-earnings-2026)\n- [SAM Expert: Microsoft Q2 FY2026 Licensing Impact](https://samexpert.com/microsoft-q2-fy2026-earnings-licensing-impact/)\n- [TechnoTrenz: Microsoft Q2 FY2026 — Record $37.5B Capex](https://technotrenz.com/news/microsoft-q2-fy2026-earnings-cloud-ai-strength-hits-81-3b-revenue-17-but-record-37-5b-capex-spooks-investors/)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "722ddb57-37f2-4164-94b7-1518b45e7129" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Here is the comprehensive research on Microsoft's Q2 FY2026 (calendar Q4 2025) earnings:\n\n---\n\n## Microsoft Q2 FY2026 Earnings Summary\n*Reported January 28, 2026 — Calendar Q4 2025*\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & YoY Growth\n\n| Metric | Result | vs. Estimate |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| **Total Revenue** | **$81.3 billion** | Beat ($80.3B est.) |\n| **YoY Growth** | **+17%** (+15% constant currency) | — |\n| **Operating Income** | $38.3 billion | +21% YoY |\n| **Operating Margin** | 47% | — |\n| **Microsoft Cloud Revenue** | $51.5 billion | +26% YoY — first time above $50B |\n\n---\n\n### 2. EPS — Actual vs. Estimates\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Non-GAAP Diluted EPS** | **$4.14** |\n| **EPS Estimate** | $3.97 |\n| **Non-GAAP EPS YoY Growth** | +24% |\n| **GAAP Diluted EPS** | $5.16 (+60%) |\n\n**Important GAAP note:** GAAP EPS was inflated by **$1.02/share** due to a net investment gain of **$7.6 billion from OpenAI**. The non-GAAP figure ($4.14) is the operative comparable. OpenAI also represented **45% of Microsoft's commercial remaining performance obligation (RPO) backlog** — a disclosure that drew significant attention.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Segment Revenue Breakdown\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY Growth |\n|---------|---------|-----------|\n| **Intelligent Cloud** | **$32.9B** | **+29%** |\n| **Productivity & Business Processes** | **$34.1B** | **+16%** (+14% CC) |\n| **More Personal Computing** | **$14.3B** | **-3%** |\n\n**Productivity & Business Processes detail:**\n- Microsoft 365 Commercial cloud: +17% (+14% CC)\n- LinkedIn: +11% (+10% CC)\n- Dynamics 365: +19% (+17% CC)\n\n**More Personal Computing detail:**\n- Search & news advertising (ex-TAC): +10%\n- Xbox content & services: -5%\n- Xbox hardware: -32%\n\n---\n\n### 4. Azure Growth Rate\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Azure & other cloud services YoY growth** | **+39%** (+38% constant currency) |\n\nThis marked an acceleration from prior quarters and was the headline result. Azure AI services represented a meaningful and growing portion of total Azure growth, with AI contributing roughly 13 percentage points of Azure's growth (per management commentary).\n\n---\n\n### 5. AI Revenue & Copilot Metrics\n\n| Metric | Figure |\n|--------|--------|\n| **AI Annual Revenue Run Rate** | **~$26 billion** |\n| **M365 Copilot paid seats** | **15 million** (+160% YoY) |\n| **M365 Copilot daily active users** | Up **10x YoY** |\n| **Conversations per M365 Copilot user** | Doubled YoY |\n| **GitHub Copilot paid subscribers** | **4.7 million** (+75% YoY) |\n| **First-party Copilot MAUs** | **150 million+** across all products |\n| **Fortune 500 with active agents** | **80%+** using Copilot Studio or Agent Builder |\n| **Purview Copilot audits** | 24 billion interactions in the quarter (+9x YoY) |\n\n---\n\n### 6. Forward Guidance (Q3 FY2026)\n\n| Metric | Guidance |\n|--------|----------|\n| **Total Revenue** | $80.65B – $81.75B |\n| **Productivity & Business Processes** | $34.25B – $34.55B |\n| **Intelligent Cloud** | $34.1B – $34.4B |\n| **Azure growth (CC)** | **37% – 38%** |\n| **Microsoft Cloud gross margin** | ~65% (down YoY due to AI infra investment) |\n| **Capital Expenditures** | Elevated; $37.5B spent in Q2 (two-thirds on short-lived assets: GPUs/CPUs) |\n\n---\n\n### 7. Key Executive Commentary\n\n**Satya Nadella (CEO):**\n- *\"We are only at the beginning phases of AI diffusion and already Microsoft has built an AI business that is larger than some of our biggest franchises.\"*\n- Framed company strategy across three layers: **\"cloud and token factory,\" \"agent platform,\" and \"high-value agentic experiences.\"**\n- Declared: *\"You can think of agents as the new apps\"* — positioning the next wave of AI as agentic workflows replacing traditional software.\n- Emphasized Microsoft's AI should be evaluated holistically (M365 Copilot + GitHub Copilot + Security Copilot + Azure AI), not just Azure AI alone.\n\n**Amy Hood (CFO):**\n- Cloud gross margin guidance of ~65% flagged as a deliberate investment decision, not a structural weakness.\n- Flagged that Azure AI capacity constraints were easing and would support re-acceleration into H2 FY2026.\n- Noted Azure guidance of 37–38% CC for Q3 was in-line with or slightly above consensus (~37.1%).\n\n---\n\n### 8. Stock Reaction\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **MSFT pre-earnings price** | ~$480.58 (Jan 27) |\n| **MSFT post-earnings price** | ~$433.50 (Jan 29) |\n| **After-hours move** | **-7%** |\n\nDespite beating on both revenue and EPS, the stock sold off sharply. Key investor concerns:\n1. **Record capex of $37.5B** — investors worried about margin compression from AI infrastructure spend\n2. **Azure guidance of 37–38%** came in roughly in-line but not above consensus, disappointing growth investors who expected acceleration\n3. **OpenAI's 45% share of RPO backlog** raised concentration/dependency concerns\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [Microsoft FY26 Q2 Press Release (official)](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q2/press-release-webcast)\n- [Microsoft FY26 Q2 Segment Results (official)](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/investor/earnings/fy-2026-q2/segment-revenues)\n- [Futurum: Microsoft Q2 FY2026 — Cloud Surpasses $50B, Azure Up 38% CC](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)\n- [CNBC: Microsoft MSFT Q2 Earnings Report 2026](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)\n- [Microsoft Source: Cloud and AI Strength Drives Second Quarter Results](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/)\n- [Yahoo Finance: Microsoft Q2 Earnings Beat Estimates](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/microsoft-q2-earnings-beat-estimates-155700958.html)\n- [Investing.com: Earnings Call Transcript Q2 2026](https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-microsoft-q2-2026-sees-strong-earnings-beat-stock-rises-93CH-4471700)\n- [Tom's Guide: Satya Nadella Q2 2026 Earnings Live](https://www.tomsguide.com/news/live/microsoft-q2-earnings-2026)\n- [SAM Expert: Microsoft Q2 FY2026 Licensing Impact](https://samexpert.com/microsoft-q2-fy2026-earnings-licensing-impact/)\n- [TechnoTrenz: Microsoft Q2 FY2026 — Record $37.5B Capex](https://technotrenz.com/news/microsoft-q2-fy2026-earnings-cloud-ai-strength-hits-81-3b-revenue-17-but-record-37-5b-capex-spooks-investors/)" ;
